31/01/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Authorities plan a major campaign to clear the streets of stray dogs following the death of a Japanese businessman in Bucharest on Sunday (29 January). 
The victim died of blood loss when a stray dog lacerated a vital artery in his leg. 
City Hall is bringing in 1,000 foreign medical students to sterilise stray dogs in the capital.
In other news Monday, the health ministry said three more people have died as a result of the cold wave, bringing the toll for January to 60. 
Eighteen of the victims were homeless. 
(Reuters, AFP - 30/01/06)
